', 'issuer': 'XIV Exporecerca Jove', 'date': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2013}}, {'title': 'Award in legal/economic issues', 'description': 'My research project was based on Human Resources, a crucial section in all companies, everywhere they are, but about which nobody wants to talk about deeply. The main reason I had to choose this subject was my own interest about the business world and all what concerns to it.
It was, with any doubt, necessary to read specialized books about the matter in order to get a total reliability in my final opinion. The book “Gestión de Personas” by Miquel Porret Gelabert, who is Doctor in Laws, Social Graduated and Diplomated in Human Resources helped me a lot in my work research. Of course I also looked for news in specialized virtual newspapers and I had the greatest opportunity to get in touch with different Companies, whose Human Resources Directors, with their experience and knowledge about the subject helped me in order to have a more real vision about Human Resources.
The question that I asked myself was: Do Private Companies give more importance to the training of their staff and also to the communications methods than Public Statements?
Throughout my work, making interviews and surveys, I had the opportunity to think about several senses of “communication and staff training”.My last conclusion was that Private Companies, “as they have not to follow specific legal rules”, take more care about the mentioned two functions than the Public Statements.
